送你防尘纸，该说什么？

162
00:10:27,22 --> 00:10:31,49
Wait,there's more. See,the contact paper is to go...
还有呢，你看跟它搭配的…

163
00:10:31,76 --> 00:10:33,89
...in your brand new drawer!
就是你的新抽屉！

164
00:10:36,60 --> 00:10:38,93
See,the drawer actually goes in my dresser.
看，其实这个抽屉 正好与我的梳妆台搭配

165
00:10:39,93 --> 00:10:42,66
You didn't have to do this.
你不用这么做啊

166
00:10:43,14 --> 00:10:44,26
Yes,I did.
对，我要这么做

167
00:10:44,47 --> 00:10:46,94
Yes,I did. Because you're my girlfriend...
是的，我要这么做 因为你是我的女朋友

168
00:10:47,17 --> 00:10:50,01
...and that's what girlfriends should get.
而女朋友就该得到这些

169
00:10:52,11 --> 00:10:54,60
Well,I gotta buy a vowel...
我得求救兵了…

170
00:10:56,28 --> 00:10:58,91
... because,oh,my God!
因为…我的天啊

171
00:11:00,19 --> 00:11:02,28
Who would've thought that someday...
谁会想的到，有一天…

172
00:11:02,49 --> 00:11:05,62
... Chandler Bing would buy me a drawer?
钱德宾会买个抽屉给我？

173
00:11:06,99 --> 00:11:08,09
Well,not me.
我可想不到

174
00:11:10,00 --> 00:11:13,26
But that's what's happened. And there's more.
但事实就是这样 而且还不只如此

175
00:11:15,27 --> 00:11:17,00
We should take a trip.
我们应该去旅行

176
00:11:17,71 --> 00:11:18,76
We should?
我们该这么做？

177
00:11:19,01 --> 00:11:21,60
We're a couple, and that's what couples do.
我们是情侣，情侣就该这样

178
00:11:22,34 --> 00:11:24,31
And I wanna meet your parents.
我还要去见你爸妈

179
00:11:24,51 --> 00:11:27,38
We should take a trip with your parents!
我们应该跟你爸妈一起去旅行

180
00:11:31,52 --> 00:11:36,01
I don't think we need to because you're tripping me out right now!
我想不用了 因为你已快把我搞迷糊了

181
00:11:37,02 --> 00:11:38,01
Are you okay?
你还好吗？

182
00:11:38,23 --> 00:11:39,21
No,I am.
我很好

183
00:11:39,96 --> 00:11:41,86
I actually am! This is amazing.
我真的很好 真是太不可思议了

184
00:11:42,13 --> 00:11:45,29
My entire life,I have feared this place.
我一生都在害怕这个时刻

185
00:11:45,57 --> 00:11:48,19
And now that I'm here,it's like, what was the big deal?
但现在时候到了 我却觉得没什么大不了

186
00:11:48,40 --> 00:11:52,34
I could probably say,"Let's move in together," and I'd be okay.
我可能会说“我们同居吧” 却还是若无其事

187
00:11:52,81 --> 00:11:55,14
You probably want us to move in together?
你可能想跟我一起住？

188
00:11:56,34 --> 00:11:59,54
-lt doesn't scare me! -Yeah,well it scares me!
我竟不会因此而害怕 是啊，但我会害怕！

189
00:11:59,81 --> 00:12:03,58
I'm not even divorced yet! You just invited me over here for pasta...
我根本还没离婚！ 你只是邀我来吃意大利面…

190
00:12:03,85 --> 00:12:06,91
...and now you're talking about moving in together.
而现在你就在说 要住在一起的事…

191
00:12:07,19 --> 00:12:09,02
And I wasn't even that hungry.
我其实还不太饿

192
00:12:09,22 --> 00:12:13,18
You know what? It's getting really late,and I should just
你知道吗？时间有点晚了 我最好先…

193
00:12:13,43 --> 00:12:16,36
Don't go! I've scared you! I've said too much!
别走，我吓着你了！ 我说太多了！

194
00:12:16,56 --> 00:12:19,66
I'm hopeless and awkward and desperate for love!
对于爱情，我是无药可救 笨拙却又充满渴望

195
00:12:26,77 --> 00:12:28,50
Hey,Janice,it's me.
珍妮丝，是我

196
00:12:30,01 --> 00:12:33,91
I wanted to apologize in advance for having chased you down the street.
我只是想在到街上追你前 先跟你道歉

197
00:12:41,02 --> 00:12:43,32
Here you go,honey. This will help.
拿去吧，甜心 应该有帮助的

198
00:12:44,13 --> 00:12:46,12
So I catch up to her and she says...
我追上她，然后她说…

199
00:12:46,36 --> 00:12:49,82
...this relationship's going too fast and we have to slow down.
这段感情发展太快 我们得放慢脚步

200
00:12:50,03 --> 00:12:51,66
That is never good.
这样绝不是好现象

201
00:12:51,87 --> 00:12:53,20
Then I got all...
于是我就变得…

202
00:12:54,17 --> 00:12:55,64
... needy and clingy.
很空虚又很黏人

203
00:12:56,47 --> 00:13:00,27
Wait a minute. Maybe it's not so bad. How did you leave it?
等等，或许不算太糟 你们怎么结束的？

204
00:13:00,51 --> 00:13:02,50
She said she'd call me.
她说她会再打给我

205
00:13:04,81 --> 00:13:06,21
Oh,God.
天啊

206
00:13:06,71 --> 00:13:08,88
Welcome to our side of the tunnel.
恭喜你到我们这一国来

207
00:13:10,18 --> 00:13:12,48
This ice cream tastes like crap, by the way.
对了，这个冰淇淋味道好烂

208
00:13:12,72 --> 00:13:16,21
Well,it's that low-cal-nondairy-soymilk junk.
因为这是低卡无乳脂 豆浆制的假冰淇淋

209
00:13:16,46 --> 00:13:19,39
We save the real stuff for the truly terminal cases.
我们把真正的留到 实在无法挽留了才吃

210
00:13:20,19 --> 00:13:23,82
When you're getting screwed over all the time,you gotta switch to low fat.
若你一直被搞得一团糟 你就要换成低脂的

211
00:13:24,13 --> 00:13:25,19
Yeah,you do.
没错，你得这么做

212
00:13:26,17 --> 00:13:28,73
You don't think I'm terminal?
你不认为我已无法挽留了？

213
00:13:28,97 --> 00:13:32,70
Not at all. You're not terminal. We just need some damage control.
不尽然，你并非无法挽留 我们只要防止事情恶化

214
00:13:32,91 --> 00:13:34,81
Okay. Should I call her?
好，我该打电话给她吗？

215
00:13:37,81 --> 00:13:41,30
It's a critical time. If you feel yourself reaching for that phone...
这段时间很重要，一旦你发现 自己的手又伸向电话…

216
00:13:41,55 --> 00:13:43,98
...go shopping,get your butt in a bubble bath.
你就去买鞋子 不然就洗个泡泡浴

217
00:13:44,19 --> 00:13:47,81
If you want her back, you have got to start acting aloof.
若你希望她回来 你就得开始表现冷漠

218
00:13:48,09 --> 00:13:50,08
She has to know you're not needy.
她必须知道 你不是那么需要她

219
00:13:50,32 --> 00:13:51,92
So what you have to do is...
所以你要做的就是…

220
00:13:52,23 --> 00:13:55,09
...you have to accidentally run into her on purpose...
假装不经意地碰到她…

221
00:13:55,33 --> 00:13:57,16
...and then act aloof.
然后表现得很冷漠

222
00:13:58,83 --> 00:14:00,86
So I'm not gonna lose her?
这样我就不会失去她了？

223
00:14:01,67 --> 00:14:04,16
Oh,honey,you're not a total loser.
甜心，你不是个弱者啊

224
00:14:07,74 --> 00:14:09,90
I said,"So I'm not gonna lose her?"
我是说 “我就不会失去她了？”

225
00:14:17,79 --> 00:14:18,84
Guess who's here!
看看谁来了！

226
00:14:19,09 --> 00:14:22,06
It's the toughest guy in Toyland,Ben!
是玩具王国里 最勇敢的人，班！

227
00:14:22,29 --> 00:14:26,23
Real American hero I'm G.I. Joe!
真正的美国英雄 我是美国大兵！

228
00:14:26,46 --> 00:14:28,95
Drop the Barbie. Drop the Barbie.
把芭比娃娃放下…

229
00:14:29,20 --> 00:14:30,56
G.I. Joe?
美国大兵？

230
00:14:30,87 --> 00:14:32,77
You really think he'll fall for that?
你真的觉得他会 喜欢那玩意儿？

231
00:14:34,03 --> 00:14:35,02
G.I. Joe?
美国大兵？

232
00:14:35,24 --> 00:14:36,40
Cool! Can I play?
好棒，我可以玩吗？

233
00:14:39,11 --> 00:14:42,80
Look,Ben! It's a toy that protects U.S. oil interests overseas!
班，你看，这个玩具 保护了美国海外油股！

234
00:14:43,08 --> 00:14:44,31
Go,Joe!
加油，大兵！

235
00:14:47,82 --> 00:14:49,94
-There you are! -No,it's not. Sorry.
菲比，你在这儿啊 不，我不是，抱歉

236
00:14:50,22 --> 00:14:52,91
But,Phoebe,wait,wait. Phoebe!
菲比，等等…

237
00:14:53,15 --> 00:14:56,15
Oh,Joey! Oh,okay! See,I didn't recognize you...
乔伊啊，我刚没认出你来…

238
00:14:56,42 --> 00:14:57,95
...in those pants.
因为你穿着这条裤子

239
00:14:59,89 --> 00:15:02,29
That TV movie I went in for, did you hear anything?
我参加试演的小型电影 有任何回音吗？

240
00:15:02,56 --> 00:15:04,22
I think I got a shot at it.
我想我应该很有机会的

241
00:15:04,43 --> 00:15:06,96
Yes,they called! You didn't get it!
对，他们打来了 你没有入选

242
00:15:07,40 --> 00:15:11,17
Okay? I mean,you didn't get it. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
可以吗？我是说你落选了 对不起…

243
00:15:11,47 --> 00:15:13,84
That's okay. These things happen.
没关系 这种事本来就会发生

244
00:15:14,11 --> 00:15:16,94
But they shouldn't happen. You know what?
但是不应该发生，你知道吗？

245
00:15:17,18 --> 00:15:19,27
You're in a terrible, terrible business.
你进的这一行 真的好可怕

246
00:15:20,51 --> 00:15:24,08
I don't want to be the person who makes you look like that.
我不想成为 那个让你难过的人

247
00:15:24,29 --> 00:15:26,31
I'm okay. See?
我没事的，你看

248
00:15:28,16 --> 00:15:30,49
Now you're sad and creepy.
你看起来很难过 让人很害怕

249
00:15:31,03 --> 00:15:32,58
I'm sorry. I quit.
我很抱歉，我要辞职

250
00:15:33,33 --> 00:15:37,13
No,no,you can't quit! You're the best agent I ever had.
不，你不能辞职！ 你是我遇过最好的经纪人

251
00:15:37,43 --> 00:15:40,83
Rejection is part of being an actor. You can't take it personal.
当一个演员本来就会被拒绝 你不能过于自责

252
00:15:41,10 --> 00:15:45,66
They said they'd never met an ltalian actor with a worse ltalian accent.
他们说没遇过一个意大利演员 有这么怪的意大利腔

253
00:15:46,27 --> 00:15:47,80
They actually said that?
他们真的这么说？

254
00:15:48,01 --> 00:15:51,94
Oh,God,there's that face again. See? I can't do this job!
天啊，又是那种表情 你看，我不能做这个工作

255
00:15:52,21 --> 00:15:54,34
This is why you have to do this job!
这就是为何你得做这份工作

256
00:15:54,55 --> 00:15:55,78
Agents always lie.
经纪人都得说谎

257
00:15:55,98 --> 00:15:58,95
Estelle just says stuff like, "They went another way."
艾斯特总是说 “他们要另一种方式”

258
00:15:59,19 --> 00:16:00,98
But this? I can use this.
但是这一点嘛，我可以改进

259
00:16:01,19 --> 00:16:04,02
I can work on a new accent.
我可以学一种新的腔调

260
00:16:05,03 --> 00:16:08,15
Yeah,okay. If it helps you,okay. Yeah.
好，若对你有帮助，那就好了

261
00:16:08,40 --> 00:16:10,80
You'll never get me,Joe!
你抓不到我，士兵！

262
00:16:24,85 --> 00:16:26,21
No,thank you.
不用了，谢谢

263
00:16:35,26 --> 00:16:37,05
What are you doing here?
你在这里干什么？

264
00:16:37,69 --> 00:16:39,39
Just a bit of shopping.
只是买买东西而已

265
00:16:39,66 --> 00:16:40,99
How have you been?
你还好吗？

266
00:16:42,56 --> 00:16:44,59
Are you being British?
你在装英国腔吗？

267
00:16:46,90 --> 00:16:48,23
Not anymore.
再也不会了

268
00:16:49,37 --> 00:16:52,50
Why are you shopping here? You don't live in this neighborhood.
你怎么在这里买东西？ 你又不住在这一带

269
00:16:52,84 --> 00:16:55,24
Were you here waiting for me?
你是不是在这里等我？

270
00:16:59,05 --> 00:17:00,04
I'm just...
我只是…

271
00:17:00,68 --> 00:17:03,34
... picking up some things for a party.
要买一点派对用的东西

272
00:17:05,29 --> 00:17:06,38
Barley?
大麦？

273
00:17:07,25 --> 00:17:09,25
What kind of party serves barley?
什么样的派对会供应大麦？

274
00:17:09,46 --> 00:17:12,58
I'm sorry if my friends aren't as sophisticated as yours.
很抱歉，我的朋友 不像你朋友那么有水准

275
00:17:14,26 --> 00:17:15,42
Where is this party?
派对在哪里举行？

276
00:17:15,63 --> 00:17:16,62
Here in Chelsea.
就在雀儿喜

277
00:17:17,13 --> 00:17:18,56
Whose party is it?
是谁办的派对

278
00:17:18,77 --> 00:17:19,89
A woman's.
一个女人

279
00:17:20,10 --> 00:17:21,09
What woman?
哪个女人？

280
00:17:22,60 --> 00:17:23,76
Chelsea.
雀儿喜

281
00:17:25,77 --> 00:17:29,04
Either you're seeing somebody behind my back...
你要不是背着我跟别人约会…

282
00:17:29,24 --> 00:17:31,87
...which would make you the world's biggest jerk...
然后成了世界第一混蛋…

283
00:17:32,08 --> 00:17:34,45
...or you're pretending to see somebody...
不然就是你假装跟别人约会…

284
00:17:34,65 --> 00:17:38,08
...which makes you so pathetic I could cry right here!
让你成为最可悲的人 我会立刻在此为你哭泣

285
00:17:38,39 --> 00:17:41,91
So which of these two guys do you want to be?
这两种男人，你想当哪一种？

286
00:17:42,96 --> 00:17:44,72
Can I be that guy?
我可以当那个人吗？

287
00:17:47,33 --> 00:17:51,73
Okay,we got some more good rejections. Lots of stuff to work on.
我们收到很多善意的拒绝 有很多地方要改进

288
00:17:52,77 --> 00:17:53,79
Okay. Shoot.
好，说吧

289
00:17:54,07 --> 00:17:56,76
Okay. Oh,the zoo commercial.
好，那个动物园广告

290
00:17:57,00 --> 00:17:57,99
I didn't get it?
我没得到那个角色？

291
00:17:58,31 --> 00:18:02,14
They said that you "weren't believable as a human being."
他们说你简直不像个人类

292
00:18:03,28 --> 00:18:05,30
So you can work on that.
所以你可以针对这一点改进

293
00:18:06,31 --> 00:18:07,30
Great.
很好

294
00:18:07,78 --> 00:18:08,77
What else?
还有呢？

295
00:18:08,98 --> 00:18:12,58
The off-Broadway-play people said that you were "pretty but dumb."
那些小剧场的人 说你很好看，可是很笨

296
00:18:13,19 --> 00:18:15,68
Oh,no wait. I'm sorry. That's "pretty dumb."
等等，对不起 他们是说你非常笨

297
00:18:16,42 --> 00:18:18,62
Look,it's okay,no,no,no. Really.
看，没关系啊 不…是真的

298
00:18:18,86 --> 00:18:19,92
Look...
听着…

299
00:18:20,33 --> 00:18:22,45
... I really appreciate this...
我很感谢你…

300
00:18:23,33 --> 00:18:25,49
... but I'm gonna have to go back to Estelle.
但我还是回去找艾斯特好了

301
00:18:26,47 --> 00:18:29,37
Don't get me wrong. You're a better agent than she is...
别误会 你当经纪人当得比她好…

302
00:18:29,67 --> 00:18:33,33
... but at least with her,I don't want to blow my pretty dumb brains out.
至少我跟着她 我这非常笨的脑袋还保得住

303
00:18:34,64 --> 00:18:36,54
Yeah,no,I understand.
是的，不，我能了解

304
00:18:36,78 --> 00:18:38,30
You do? Thanks. Okay.
你可以吗？谢谢你

305
00:18:38,65 --> 00:18:39,63
Sorry.
抱歉

306
00:18:43,48 --> 00:18:44,61
Wait a minute.
等一下

307
00:18:44,85 --> 00:18:46,11
Wait a minute.
等一下

308
00:18:46,35 --> 00:18:49,69
Did you make all that stuff up to get out of being my agent?
你是不是故意编这些出来 就不用当我的经纪人了？

309
00:18:49,96 --> 00:18:51,32
Oh,he caught me.
被你发现了

310
00:18:53,73 --> 00:18:55,46
I am so busted!
我完蛋了！

311
00:18:56,63 --> 00:18:58,83
That's what I suspected!
我早就这么怀疑了

312
00:19:02,37 --> 00:19:04,30
And then I just,you know...
然后我只好…

313
00:19:05,17 --> 00:19:08,47
...threw the bag of barley at her and ran out of the store.
把一袋大麦丢到她身上 然后逃出那间店

314
00:19:09,08 --> 00:19:12,84
My God,Chandler,we said be "aloof," not "a doof."
天啊，我们叫你表现冷漠 不是像个笨蛋

315
00:19:14,52 --> 00:19:17,35
I've actually ruined this,haven't l?
我这次真的搞砸了，对吧？

316
00:19:18,85 --> 00:19:20,91
Is it time for the good ice cream now?
这次可以吃 真正的冰淇淋了吗？

317
00:19:21,66 --> 00:19:22,99
Yeah,it is.
没错，可以了

318
00:19:23,66 --> 00:19:26,85
You know what? Everything's gonna be okay.
你知道吗？一切都没问题的

319
00:19:33,87 --> 00:19:35,99
Can you hold on for a second?
珍妮丝，你可以等一下吗？

320
00:19:37,60 --> 00:19:38,70
What do I do?
好，我该怎么办？

321
00:19:38,91 --> 00:19:40,84
I don't know. This is unprecedented.
我不知道，这是史无前例的

322
00:19:41,07 --> 00:19:43,67
If we did what you did, a man would never call.
若我们做出像你一样的事 男人绝不会再打来了

323
00:19:44,61 --> 00:19:48,07
I got it! Pretend you just woke up. That'll throw her off!
我知道了，假装你刚睡醒 这样就可以摆脱她了

324
00:19:48,28 --> 00:19:50,41
-Be sleepy! -Yes! And grumpy!
睡意惺忪的样子！ 对，脾气暴躁的感觉！

325
00:19:50,68 --> 00:19:53,28
What are you? Stop naming dwarfs!
你们怎么…？ 别开始数小矮人的名字

326
00:19:58,59 --> 00:20:01,25
I'm so glad that you called.
我很高兴你打来

327
00:20:02,46 --> 00:20:06,87
I know I've been acting really weird lately...
我知道我最近的表现很怪…

328
00:20:08,20 --> 00:20:11,23
...and it's just because I'm crazy about you...
那是因为我太爱你了

329
00:20:14,04 --> 00:20:18,21
...and I just got stupid and scared...
我就变得很蠢，又很害怕…

330
